---
description: English-only rule for all file content
globs: **/*
alwaysApply: true
---
ALL content written into ANY file MUST be English: source code, comments,
UI strings, README, .cursorrules, .mdc rules, YAML comments, JSON keys and
values, CSS class names, identifiers, and commit messages.

Turkish (or any non-English language) is allowed ONLY in chat explanations
to the user — NEVER inside a file.

Forbidden inside files: Turkish-specific letters — c-cedilla, g-breve,
dotted-i and dotless-i, o-umlaut, u-umlaut, s-cedilla (upper and lower case).
Plain rule: any non-ASCII letter is forbidden. If you think in Turkish,
translate to English BEFORE writing it into a file.

Verification command (must pass): node scripts/check-language.mjs --strict
